# Context documentation (agent upkeep)

This repo maintains modular agent docs under **`context/`** (see **`context/README.md`** for the index).

## When to update

After a substantive change to **any** of the following, update the **matching** context file(s) in the same change set (or immediately after), not only in code:

| Change area | Prefer updating |
|-------------|-------------------|
| `server.ts`, routes, render options, webhooks | `context/api-server.md` |
| `src/remotion/*`, composition id, duration, fps | `context/remotion.md` |
| Template components, `templateId`, `data` shapes | `context/templates.md` |
| `EffectsOverlay`, branding fields | `context/effects.md` |
| n8n workflows, automation payload | `context/integration-n8n.md` |
| Scripts, tests, tsconfig, deploy paths | `context/development.md` |
| New top-level concern or many files touched | `context/overview.md` and/or `context/README.md` index |

## What “update” means

- Keep **field names**, **defaults**, **endpoints**, and **file paths** accurate.
- If behavior is intentionally removed or deprecated, remove or strike it from docs in the same pass.
- Do **not** duplicate long schemas in multiple files; cross-link to **`templates.md`** or **`api-server.md`**.

## Lessons

If a mistake was made (wrong assumption, wrong path, integration mismatch), add a short dated entry to **`context/lesson-learned.md`** at the **top** of the entries list, using the template in that file.

## Scope

This rule is **file-scoped** (`**/*.{ts,tsx,json}`): it applies when those files are relevant to the chat, not when you are only editing `context/*.md` or other docs.

Skip doc-only edits for **trivial** edits (typos, formatting-only) unless they touch documented behavior. For **any** API or template contract change, treat context updates as **required**.
